translated: Mouchard, Gustaf Sigfrid, clergyman, archpriest, Ullervad, born on May 12, 1881 in Gösislliundia, Skaraborg County, son of Johan M. and Sofia Högberg. Married on the 13th of an unknown month to Hedwig SuiitdieüLn. Children: Ami!a-LiiS’a, born in 1914. Started studying theology in Sikara in 1904, completed theological studies in Lund in 1905, ordained deacon in 1908, ordained priest and served in various positions in Skara until 1918. Became curate in Fallköping in 1908, preacher assistant in Skara cathedral in 1909, chaplain in Lagniannesd in 1911, elected parish priest of Ullervad in 1923, appointed archpriest of Mia-råesitadisi in an unknown year. Chairman of the pastoral council and church board, chairman of the Skara board. Awarded the Order of the Lion of Sweden in 1944.
